e the viewer cannot help reimaging the devastation through the lenses of history, aestheticization, or voyeurism, these images at least allow us to approach the reality of ruins and grasp the larger issue of targeting civilians in modern warfare for what it is. Refreshingly accessible and deeply personal, Dark Lens is a compelling look at the role images play in constructing memories of war.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aCivilians in warzGermany. 0aRuins in art. 0aRuins, ModernzGermany. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xDestruction and pillagezGermany. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xMoral and ethical aspects. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zGermanyvArt and the war. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zGermanyxAerial operations, Allied. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zGermanyxInfluence. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zGermanyxPhotography. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zGermanyxPsychological aspects. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aGermany during and after WWII.  aThe Resistance.  abombing.  aethics.  aliterature.  amemory.  aphotography.  aruins gazing.  asuffering.  awitnessing.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishz978311061017808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226625775423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226625775.jpg  a978-3-11-061017-8  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 English